scene.message:
Maki: This shop is run by the{nl}
uncle of a friend of mine,{nl}
a boy named Tadashi.{waitkey}{clearbox}Tadashi gets along terribly{nl}
with a transfer student, a{nl}
girl named Tamaki.{waitkey}They won't even speak to{nl}
each other anymore...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Tadashi's uncle, huh...{nl}
Doesn't seem all that{nl}
different from our town.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Forgive me for saying{nl}
so, but does the medicine{nl}
here really work, I wonder.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Baby goods are all so{nl}
cute. Just looking at them is{nl}
fun.{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: Welcome to Satomi{nl}
Tadashi! Call me Sato-chan,{nl}
okay~♥{waitkey}Now, let's do some business~!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: I'm feeling blue{nl}
today.{waitkey}At times like this, all you{nl}
can do is go to the bar and{nl}
talk about the Queen's{nl}
paintings, right~{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: The Queen's finally{nl}
gone. Time to raise a toast{nl}
at the bar!{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: You can't go in{nl}
there~ Even "just a peek" is{nl}
a no-no~!{waitkey}{ret}
